Meaning of the name Swati

Swati comes from Sanskrit and has several related meanings:

A Nakshatra (Star)

Swati is the 15th Nakshatra in Indian astrology

It is associated with independence, freedom, and movement

Pure / Clean / Bright

The word Swāti can imply purity and clarity

A drop of rain 

In Indian tradition, Swati rain is believed to be pure and powerful, symbolizing growth and positivity

Associated deity

The ruling deity of Swati Nakshatra is Vayu (Wind God)

This represents flexibility, intelligence, and independence

Common traits associated with the name Swati

People named Swati are often described as:

Independent

Intelligent

Adaptable

Kind-hearted

Freedom-loving

Usage

Gender: Mostly female, but can be unisex

Common in: India, Nepal, and among Indian communities worldwide

